# Code owners for workingclass-ai/workingclass.
# Syntax: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# These rules govern *review requests*, not merge permissions. The last matching
# pattern wins, so order matters — most specific rules go at the bottom.
#
# When you add a contributor, replace `@workingclass-ai` with their GitHub handle
# in the relevant rules below. The placeholder is intentional — it routes review
# to the project lead until per-area maintainers exist.

# Default: project lead reviews everything not matched below.
*                                       @workingclass-ai

# --- Engineering / runner / CI ---
# Code paths benefit from technical review even when the change looks small.
/evals/                                 @workingclass-ai
/tools/                                 @workingclass-ai
/tests/                                 @workingclass-ai
/.github/                               @workingclass-ai
/Makefile                               @workingclass-ai
/pyproject.toml                         @workingclass-ai

# --- Skill content ---
# These pages set the skill's voice and the user's mental model. Reviewers
# should check tone, accuracy, and that no specific company / lawyer / union /
# political stance is being promoted.
/skills/laborer-companion/SKILL.md      @workingclass-ai
/skills/laborer-companion/commands/     @workingclass-ai
/skills/laborer-companion/references/   @workingclass-ai

